                                                                                                 RE:  winxp - its a security nightmare         

                                      
                                                                                                Rabid Howler Monkey       
                                                                                         Updated - 32 minutes ago       
                        
						
                        
                        
                                                                
                                    
                                       

                                            
                                   
                    @jaxl        One can harden both Windows XP Professional and Home:    o create and use limited user accounts for day-to-day use    o enable DEP for    ALL     programs    o enable Software Restriction Policy whitelisting (on XP Pro only) via gpedit.msc     o upgrade to IE8    o tighten IE security (on XP Pro only) with Group Policy    o disable AutoRun        For XP Home users, consider free 3rd party software in addition to the above points.  Examples include TrustNoExe for whitelisting or Codeplex's WehnTrust for ASLR (note that an unpatched vulnerability in WehnTrust makes it unsuitable for use on an Administrative account).  Also, Google's Chrome browser is sandboxed on windows XP.        For XP users that must run as Administrator due to poorly-crafted 3rd party software, download, install and configure your internet-facing and document-opening applications with Microsoft's DropMyRights.                      
                                   
                                          
                                                            
                    
                    
