                                                                                                 You probably disagreed on Vista too...         

                                      
                                                                                                jasonp@...       
                                                                                59 minutes ago       
                        
						
                        
                        
                                                                
                                    
                                       

                                            
                                   
                    Windows 7 is eventually going to overtake XP and will rule the roost for the next 10 years or so.  This isn't an if, this is a certainty.  Corporate America is going to look at the training costs and loss of productivity involved with implementing an entirely new user interface and say "Thanks, but no thanks."  The enterprise can swallow incremental changes, but Windows 8 and Metro changes the entire playing field.  It's a TCO nightmare.  The times might be a changin', but business is still business and what matters most is the bottom line.  Had Microsoft decided to take baby steps towards a new UI, Windows 8 would have been a strong contender for the next Microsoft behemoth.  Windows 7 is already poised to assume that role and Windows 8 doesn't appear to have a chance of supplanting it.                      
                                   
                                          
                                                            
                    
                    
