                                                                                                 RIP XP         

                                      
                                                                                                itpro_z       
                                                                                1 hr ago       
                        
						
                        
                        
                                                                
                                    
                                       

                                            
                                   
                    Personally, I am counting the days until XP is gone from our network.  Most of our support issues are for XP machines, whether it is removing viruses, dealing with instability issues, or incompatibility with modern software.  We are replacing those machines as fast as we can and our budget supports, but will continue to deal with XP for at least another year.  Windows 7 has proven to be an excellent OS, both fast and stable to a degree never approached by XP.  We have even deviated from our long held belief that you don't upgrade OSs on older machines and have wiped many XP and Vista systems to install Windows 7.  In every case, the computer ran far better with 7 than it ever did with XP.        Windows 8?  I don't buy the hand wringing over 8 that some here seem to exhibit.  (No Start button?  OMG, it's the end of the world!)  We will begin our testing of 8 not long after it appears.  If it is as polished as 7 was when it hit I see no reason to delay rolling it out on new systems.  Some of you so called IT people must have majored in Drama in school.  It's just an OS, people!  Change is the one constant in what we do.                      
                                   
                                          
                                                            
                    
                    
